definition.value: An organosulfur compound in which a thiol group, -SH, is attached to a carbon atom of any aliphatic or aromatic moiety.
A monovalent inorganic anion obtained by deprotonation of phosphorous acid.
A divalent inorganic anion resulting from the removal of a proton from two of the hydroxy groups of phosphorous acid.
A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of both protons from diphosphonic acid.
A trivalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of all three protons from peroxyphosphoric acid.
An organic thiosulfate compound having an S-alkyl substituent.
A  flavan glycoside that is (2S)-flavan substituted by a methoxy group at position 4', hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 5' and a beta-D-glucopyranosyloxy group at position 3 respectively.
A sulfinyl halide in which both of the halide atoms are chorines.
